Executive Profile
Simon D. Medley  Executive Vice President, Great Lakes Chemical CorporationAgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 0 Board Members in 0 different organizations across 4 different industries.50--
Background

		Mr. Simon D. Medley served as an Executive Vice President of Industrial Performance Products & Great Lakes Solutions (alternate name Great Lakes Chemical Corporation) at LANXESS Solutions US Inc. since October 20, 2014 until April 21, 2017 and also served as its Head of Industrial Performance Products Segment. Mr. Medley served as the President of Petroleum Additives Business at Chemtura Corporation from October 2012 to September 2013 and served as its General Manager ... of Petroleum Additives Business. Mr. Medley served as Managing Director of Cognis Corporation. He served as Group Vice President of Care Chemicals and Formulators at BASF Corp. He was a Member of Chemtura’s leadership Steering Team. Mr. Medley joined Chemtura in 2012 after 18 years with BASF, where he built a track record of international success in diverse industries leading sustainable, profitable growth through market-driven innovation, strategic portfolio management and transformational cultural change. He served as Senior Vice President for European Personal-Care Division at BASF SE until October 2012. From 2004 to 2010, Mr. Medley engineered significant profitability improvements as Senior Vice President of BASF’s Fine Chemicals and Care Chemicals North American business units successively, including the integration of Engelhard and Ciba operations. In 2011, he returned to Europe to lead the reverse integration of Cognis’ Personal Care business as Senior Vice President and Managing Director of BASF Personal Care & Nutrition GmbH. He started his career with ICI in the U.K. in 1988. Mr. Medley served as a Director of The American Cleaning Institute (alternate name The Soap and Detergent Association). Mr. Medley served various board positions in international industry associations. Mr. Medley earned a Bachelor’s Degree with honors in Chemical Engineering at the University of Teesside, U.K.Read Full Background




